}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b 37-39.}{\plain \fs24   There has been a lengthy dispute in the commentary tradition as to whether or not \softline
Dante has invented the neutral angels or is reflecting a medieval tradition that had itself \softline
'invented' them (since they are not, properly speaking, biblical in origin).  This is presented at \softline
