Rachel Jacoff (Cambridge: Harvard University Press, 1986), pp. 110-18.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b 40-42.}{\plain \fs24   To what does the adjective }{\plain \fs24 \i rei}{\plain \fs24  ('evil') refer?  The neutral angels (v. 38) are the \softline
antecedent of the pronoun }{\plain \fs24 \i li}{\plain \fs24  in vv. 40 and 41.  It seems clear that this is also true with respect to \softline
