I-III}{\plain \fs24  [Florence: Sansoni, 1967]), pp. 425-27.  Most today, including Mazzoni, take Charon's \softline
formulation to refer to Dante's eventual passage to Purgatory aboard the angel-guided ship that \softline
we see in }{\plain \fs24 \i Purgatorio}{\plain \fs24  II.41.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \par
